What is the purpose of the `migrate_completeimporttransaction` command in Verus?
The `migrate_completeimporttransaction` command is used to extend a proof generated on an asset chain to a target chain proof root. This is typically used in cross-chain import transactions.

migrate_completeimporttransaction importTx

Takes a cross chain import tx with proof generated on assetchain and extends proof to target chain proof root
What type of transaction does the `migrate_completeimporttransaction` command work with?
The `migrate_completeimporttransaction` command works with cross-chain import transactions.

migrate_completeimporttransaction importTx

Takes a cross chain import tx with proof generated on assetchain and extends proof to target chain proof root
What does the `migrate_completeimporttransaction` command do to the proof generated on an asset chain?
The `migrate_completeimporttransaction` command extends the proof generated on an asset chain to a target chain proof root.

migrate_completeimporttransaction importTx

Takes a cross chain import tx with proof generated on assetchain and extends proof to target chain proof root
